The paper proposes a method for neural architecture search (NAS) that involves designing an architecture-intensive search space and training a HyperNetwork to predict weights of convolution kernels for neural architectures in the search space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these are the areas where NAS is commonly used. Additionally, the paper involves training a HyperNetwork, which is a type of neural network used for meta-learning, suggesting that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimizing the search process, which may suggest that it belongs to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves predicting weights for neural architectures, which may suggest that it belongs to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category, as this is an area where weight prediction is commonly used.
